com.jackbe.jbp.sas.sg.model
Class ServiceRequestObject

java.lang.Object
  com.jackbe.jbp.sas.sg.model.ServiceRequestObject
Direct Known Subclasses:
JUMPRequest
public class ServiceRequestObject
extends java.lang.Object

A request object for the Presto Mashup Server. This is a Java object for requests. It also serializes itself to create a request in the JUMP (JackBe Universal Message Protocol) protocol expected by the Mashup Server.

ServiceRequestObject instances can contain optional JUMP headers to enable optional behavior or to send additional information to the service. Optional headers include:

  • authToken = an authentication token for requests from clients that have already logged in. The token to use with this header is returned in the login method response. See also username.

  • debug = true | false flag to control debugging messages.

  • excludeJUMPEnvelope = true | false flag that controls whether the JUMP response returns a full JUMP message or returns just the body of the service response. By default, this is false.

    If true, successful responses contain the body of the service response only. Unsuccessful responses set the HTTP header for a failed request and send the error message as the body of the response.

  • httpBasicAuth = an object with the user credentials to send to the service in the HTTP authentication header. This is useful for some SOAP services that require credentials in an HTTP header.

  • invId = invocation ID. This header is reserved for future use.

  • password = password for credentials for this request. See also username.

  • portType = the port type name to use for SOAP services whose WSDL has mutliple port types.

  • resultContentType = the MIME type, such as "text plain; charset=UTF-8", to use for the result. By default, this is UTF-8. You can change this to ISO-8859-1 (Latin-1).

  • resultFormat = json (default) | xml | native. Defines the format for the response.

  • returnServiceHeaders = true | false flag to control whether HTTP headers in the service response are forwarded back to the client.

    This flag is only needed to override the default behavior defined in server configuration properties for the Mashup Server. If the server does not forward service headers by default, setting this flag in a request will ensure that HTTP headers are sent - and vice versa. The headers that can be forwarded are defined in a white list in Mashup Server configuration.

  • serviceEndpoint = the URL that should override the existing endpoint for the service in this request. Use this header to handle dynamic endpoints for services.

  • serviceHeader = an object to use as a header in the request to the service, such as SOAP headers.

  • sessionbinding = an object with one or more tokens that define portions of the response to this request that should be saved in the session. Later requests can use these tokens as input params to be resolved from session data. Session binding tokens for this header are in the form @sessionbinding.attribute-name=Xpath/to/nodes/to/save.

  • username = user name for credentials for this request. Typically, this header should be used, in combination with the password header, to log in or authenticate a new principal. Once the principal is authenticated, use the authToken header as the credentials for a request.
